sentences: Quorthon formed Bathory in 1983 when he was 17 years old, after briefly playing in the Oi! band Stridskuk, which also featured drummer Johan "Jolle" Elvén and bass player Rickard "Ribban" Bergman, who later played on early Bathory demos and in the case of Bergman, albums.

Beginning in the 1990s, Quorthon took full control of Bathory, choosing to forgo performing live in order to spend time recording music with hired musicians, as well changing style from the black metal of the 1980s to a slower, heavier style dubbed "Viking metal", due to its lyrics being focused on Norse mythology.
In 1993 Quorthon set Bathory aside and recorded and released two albums under the name "Quorthon".
The first, called Album, was released in 1994.
The final two solo releases emerged in 1997, Purity of Essence and the EP When Our Day Is Through.
On 3 June 2004, Quorthon was found dead in his apartment in Stockholm, Sweden.

sentences: Thomas Börje Forsberg (17 February 1966 – 3 June 2004), better known by the stage name Quorthon, was a Swedish singer, musician and songwriter.

Quorthon formed Bathory in 1983 when he was 17 years old, after briefly playing in the Oi! band Stridskuk, which also featured drummer Johan "Jolle" Elvén and bass player Rickard "Ribban" Bergman, who later played on early Bathory demos and in the case of Bergman, albums.
During the mid-to-late 1980s, live performances by Bathory were rare.

Beginning in the 1990s, Quorthon took full control of Bathory, choosing to forgo performing live in order to spend time recording music with hired musicians, as well changing style from the black metal of the 1980s to a slower, heavier style dubbed "Viking metal", due to its lyrics being focused on Norse mythology.
The final two solo releases emerged in 1997, Purity of Essence and the EP When Our Day Is Through.
Quorthon was buried on July 13 the same year at Sandsborgs kyrkogård in Gamla Enskede, South Stockholm.
When Our Day Is Through EP (1997)
